@Node Features "Info about InfoX"
* InfoX is CLI/Shell utility which shows informations about @{"XPK" Link XPK}
	sub-libraries.  Never run it from Workbench!

* InfoX was written in assembler, that's why it is fast and small.

* InfoX can show info about given packer(s) or all available packers.  You
	can also get info about packer's modes.

* InfoX can be interrupted by Ctrl-C.

* InfoX pauses between packers if you want
@EndNode


@Node Require "Requirements"
InfoX needs the following things:

* Kickstart v2.04 (37.175) or newer
* xpkmaster.library v2 or newer  (in LIBS: directory)
* some xpk sublibs (in LIBS:Compressors directory)

Read @{"XPK" Link XPK} documentation how to install XPK package.
@EndNode


@Node Usage
InfoX is CLI/Shell utility.  Never run it from Workbench!

InfoX	<packer(s)> [MODES] [PAUSE]

Template: PACKER/M,MODES/S,PAUSE/S

Where:
PACKER - four-letter name of the packer, for example:
	@{b}InfoX RLEN@{ub}
		shows info about @{i}xpkRLEN.library@{ui}

MODES - show also all modes available for packer(s), for example:
	@{b}InfoX NUKE MODES@{ub}
		shows info about @{i}xpkNUKE.library@{ui} with all its modes

PAUSE - wait for Return/Enter key between packers
@EndNode


